    "updated_at": "2013-10-13T17:44:41Z",
    "body": "Here's a simple ScopeGuard implementation as a library: https://gist.github.com/sfackler/6965006. Having to manually save the object in a variable isn't great, but a syntax extension to do expand\n\n``` rust\nscope!(Success) { thing }\n```\n\nto something like\n\n``` rust\nlet __scope_<FILE>_<LINE>_<COL> = ::std::scope::scope(Success, { thing });\n```\n\nshouldn't be too hard. I don't think it can be done with a `macro_rules` currently.\n",
